requestStart() - Method in class tp.pr5.RobotEngine
Requests the engine to inform the observers that the simulation starts.
The simulation finishes when the robot arrives at the space ship, the user types "QUIT", or the robot runs out of fuel
It has be called by startControllerIt and only after controller is created and all the observers have been registered.

This class represents the robot engine.
RobotEngine(City, Place, Direction) - Constructor for class tp.pr5.RobotEngine

RobotEngineObserver - Interface in tp.pr5.view.observersInterfaces
Interface which must implement all the classes "Observer", i.e., all the classes which depend of changes in the robot engine.
The robot engine will notify the changes in the robot (fuel and recycled material), will inform about communication problems, errors and when the robot wants to say something.
Finally, the engine will also notify when the user requests help and when the robot shuts down (because the robot run out of fuel or when it arrived at the spaceship) It's not obligatory write code for each update.
